NAME
	video-pane (display) - render a decoded video feed from a vid9p stream directory, compositing I420 frames through the mpeg remap24 path into the pane

INTERFACE
	display (MatrixDisplay)

READS
	<mount>/fmt	"<w> <h> i420 <fps>" — stream geometry.
	<mount>/frame	the I420 byte stream; each w*h*3/2 bytes is one
			decoded frame (see appl/cmd/vid9p.b).

WRITES
	none (renders only)

DESCRIPTION
	The mount path is a vid9p stream directory (e.g. /mnt/video/0)
	served by appl/cmd/vid9p.b over the host-decode 9P bridge
	(docs/H264-9P-BRIDGE.md).  fmt is read once for geometry; each
	Matrix update() pulls one frame from the frame file, wraps its
	bytes as a Mpegio->YCbCr and runs it through the SAME remap24
	(YCbCr->RGB24) converter the standalone vidplay/vidplay9p players
	use — there is no new pixel code.  The frame is drawn at its
	native size, centred in the pane and clipped to the pane
	rectangle, with a thin border.  A canned clip loops at end of
	stream; a live feed plays as frames arrive.  fmt/frame need not
	exist at init: the pane retries lazily and shows "no video" until
	the source appears.  Multiplex by placing one video-pane leaf per
	feed in the composition.

SEE ALSO
	vid9p (appl/cmd/vid9p.b — serves /mnt/video/<id>)
	vidplay9p (appl/mpeg — standalone windowed player, same feed)
	docs/H264-9P-BRIDGE.md, docs/MULTIPLEXED-VIDEO-SPIKE.md
